CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 17, 1963, pg. 1 reads: "Over 2,000 Join UNPC in Massive Pittsburgh Walk - Pretty Evelyn Stroud (flowered dress), employee of a local banking firm, took advantage of her lunch hour to join the pickets as they marched around the Duquesne Light Company Building on Monday. - Harris Photo."One of the protesters is carrying a sign that reads: "Stop Unfair Hiring Practices" and another has placard that has "NAACP Youth Council" at the bottom.
TitMainTitle: Protesters, including Robert Lavelle and Judge Henry Smith in center, wearing and carrying small banners reading "Let's March," marching on street in front of Duquesne Light building, Downtown
